# Frontend Development Rules

## Project Structure

- Entry point: [zen-web/src/main.tsx](mdc:zen-web/src/main.tsx)
- Root route: [zen-web/src/routes/\_\_root.tsx](mdc:zen-web/src/routes/__root.tsx)
- Route tree: [zen-web/src/routeTree.gen.ts](mdc:zen-web/src/routeTree.gen.ts) (generated, do not edit manually)
- Config files: [zen-web/package.json](mdc:zen-web/package.json), [zen-web/vite.config.ts](mdc:zen-web/vite.config.ts)
- Global style: [zen-web/src/style.css](mdc:zen-web/src/style.css)

## Code Organization

- Pages/routes in [zen-web/src/routes/](mdc:zen-web/src/routes/)
- Reusable components in [zen-web/src/components/](mdc:zen-web/src/components/)
- Admin shell layout in [zen-web/src/components/base-layout/](mdc:zen-web/src/components/base-layout/)
- API modules in [zen-web/src/api/](mdc:zen-web/src/api/)
- Shared state in [zen-web/src/store/](mdc:zen-web/src/store/)

## TypeScript Conventions

- Keep API/request/response fields in `camelCase`.
- Reuse module types under `zen-web/src/api/<module>/`.
- Avoid redefining API types in page files.

## Component Architecture

- Use functional components with hooks.
- Keep pages as composition/orchestration; move reusable UI to `components`.
- Do not mix unrelated request logic into presentational components.

## State Management

- Use Zustand for shared state (see [zen-web/src/store/useAuthStore.ts](mdc:zen-web/src/store/useAuthStore.ts) and [zen-web/src/store/useLocalStore.ts](mdc:zen-web/src/store/useLocalStore.ts)).
- Keep state close to usage; avoid unnecessary global stores.

## API Integration

- Place request logic in `zen-web/src/api/<module>/`.
- Do not write raw HTTP calls directly in route/page files.
- Keep module types next to request wrappers, for example [zen-web/src/api/system/user/types.d.ts](mdc:zen-web/src/api/system/user/types.d.ts).
- Keep API contract changes synced with backend and frontend callsites.

## Styling Guidelines

- Prefer Ant Design and Pro Components as primary UI layer.
- Tailwind is for local supplements, not as a replacement UI system.

## Routing

- Use TanStack Router file routes under [zen-web/src/routes/](mdc:zen-web/src/routes/).
- Keep route guards in root route flow (see `__root.tsx`).

## Development Tools

- Development/build entry remains `vp dev` and `vp build` via package scripts.
- `just check` executes frontend lint through `vp lint`.

## File Naming

- Keep naming consistent with existing files in `zen-web/src/`.
- Do not manually edit generated `routeTree.gen.ts`.
